replies.body:
Just played a game
Top:{{champion:86}} (Side note: Most magic damage)
Mid: {{champion:238}} 
Jungle:{{champion:91}} 
Marksman: {{champion:18}} 
Support: {{champion:40}}  (This was me.)

Somehow, the enemy built a ton of armor but didn't teamfight very well, so we kept picking them off and flipped the game that should've been a loss.

As to the Mage itemization... yeah, it is kinda lacking really. If you think about resource management, auto-attacks on mages won't always net the best results, so blowing a spell like you sometimes do on a mage can be more punishing in terms of mana if you don't maintain carefully. Also, I still believe there's a distinct lack of defense options for mages, which definitely leads to them being prime choices for being picked off. It's partly intended, but in the longer run, sustained combat mages definitely feel the brunt of less defensive options. Otherwise it's all glass cannon really, which was always partly discouraged in the past since there was always little to no counterplay to an enemy that could 1-shot you.
